    <string name="wizard_accessibility_content">In order for the Gtalk profile and your own custom profiles to work, NotiSync needs to be enabled as an Accessibility Service. This is an optional step, and NotiSync will not collect any information provided.</string>
    <string name="wizard_accessibility_enable">Enable now</string>
    <string name="wizard_accessibility_enabled">Enabled!</string>
    <string name="wizard_customprofiles_title">Custom profiles</string>
    <string name="wizard_customprofiles_content_primary">
<![CDATA[
        Creating a custom profile will allow you to forward notifications from almost any app. Here are some important things to know.<br /><br />
        
        <b>Name</b><br />
        Help yourself identify your profiles with a simple display name.<br /><br />
        
        <b>Tag</b><br />
        For every custom profile that you create, you will need to set a unique \'tag\'. Create a custom profile on your other devices with a matching tag to configure how those notifications are received.
        ]]>
    </string>
    <string name="wizard_customprofiles_content_secondary">
<![CDATA[
        If you\'ve created any custom profiles on your primary device, create a matching profile here to configure your notifications. Here are some important things to know.<br /><br />
        
        <b>Name</b><br />
        Help yourself identify your profiles with a simple display name. This name will also be used as a title for your notifications.<br /><br />
        
        <b>Tag</b><br />
        This tag must match a tag that you\'ve used on your primary device. This is how NotiSync identifies custom notifications when they are received.<br /><br />
        
        <b>Only if no internet connection</b><br />
        Enable this to only display these notifications when you do not have an internet connection. This is useful if you already have the app on this device and you don\'t want duplicate notifications while you\'re online.
        ]]>
    </string>
